verses.text_plain: The words of the Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 1The words of the Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: Vanity of vanities, saith the Preacher, vanity of vanities; all is vanity.
verses.verse_html: 2Vanity of vanities, saith the Preacher, vanity of vanities; all is vanity.

verses.text_plain: What profit hath a man of all his labour which he taketh under the sun?
verses.verse_html: 3What profit hath a man of all his labour which he taketh under the sun?

verses.text_plain: One generation passeth away, and another generation cometh: but the earth abideth for ever.
verses.verse_html: 4One generation passeth away, and another generation cometh: but the earth abideth for ever.

verses.text_plain: The sun also ariseth, and the sun goeth down, and hasteth to his place where he arose.
verses.verse_html:
5The sun also ariseth, and the sun goeth down, and hasteth to his place where he arose. ▼
▼ hasteth: Heb. panteth

verses.text_plain: The wind goeth toward the south, and turneth about unto the north; it whirleth about continually, and the wind returneth again according to his circuits.
verses.verse_html: 6The wind goeth toward the south, and turneth about unto the north; it whirleth about continually, and the wind returneth again according to his circuits.

verses.text_plain: All the rivers run into the sea; yet the sea is not full; unto the place from whence the rivers come, thither they return again.
verses.verse_html:
7All the rivers run into the sea; yet the sea is not full; unto the place from whence the rivers come, thither they return again. ▼
▼ return…: Heb. return to go

footnotes.body_html: ▼ return…: Heb. return to go

verses.text_plain: All things are full of labour; man cannot utter it: the eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.
verses.verse_html: 8All things are full of labour; man cannot utter it: the eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.

verses.text_plain: The thing that hath been, it is that which shall be; and that which is done is that which shall be done: and there is no new thing under the sun.
verses.verse_html: 9The thing that hath been, it is that which shall be; and that which is done is that which shall be done: and there is no new thing under the sun.

tokens.text: which shall be; and that which is done

verses.text_plain: Is there any thing whereof it may be said, See, this is new? it hath been already of old time, which was before us.
verses.verse_html: 10Is there any thing whereof it may be said, See, this is new? it hath been already of old time, which was before us.

verses.text_plain: There is no remembrance of former things; neither shall there be any remembrance of things that are to come with those that shall come after.
verses.verse_html: 11There is no remembrance of former things; neither shall there be any remembrance of things that are to come with those that shall come after.

verses.text_plain: I the Preacher was king over Israel in Jerusalem.
verses.verse_html: 12I the Preacher was king over Israel in Jerusalem.

verses.text_plain: And I gave my heart to seek and search out by wisdom concerning all things that are done under heaven: this sore travail hath God given to the sons of man to be exercised therewith.
verses.verse_html:
13And I gave my heart to seek and search out by wisdom concerning all things that are done under heaven: this sore travail hath God given to the sons of man to be exercised therewith. ▼
▼ to be…: or, to afflict them

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to be…: or, to afflict them
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to be…: or, to afflict them

verses.text_plain: I have seen all the works that are done under the sun; and, behold, all is vanity and vexation of spirit.
verses.verse_html: 14I have seen all the works that are done under the sun; and, behold, all is vanity and vexation of spirit.

verses.text_plain: That which is crooked cannot be made straight: and that which is wanting cannot be numbered.
verses.verse_html:
15That which is crooked cannot be made straight: and that which is wanting cannot be numbered. ▼
▼ that which is wanting: Heb. defect

footnotes.body_text: ▼ that which is wanting: Heb. defect
footnotes.body_html: ▼ that which is wanting: Heb. defect

verses.text_plain: I communed with mine own heart, saying, Lo, I am come to great estate, and have gotten more wisdom than all they that have been before me in Jerusalem: yea, my heart had great experience of wisdom and knowledge.
verses.verse_html:
16I communed with mine own heart, saying, Lo, I am come to great estate, and have gotten more wisdom than all they that have been before me in Jerusalem: yea, my heart had great experience of wisdom and knowledge. ▼
▼ had…: Heb. had seen much

tokens.text: Lo, I am come to great estate

footnotes.body_html: ▼ had…: Heb. had seen much

verses.text_plain: And I gave my heart to know wisdom, and to know madness and folly: I perceived that this also is vexation of spirit.
verses.verse_html: 17And I gave my heart to know wisdom, and to know madness and folly: I perceived that this also is vexation of spirit.

verses.text_plain: For in much wisdom is much grief: and he that increaseth knowledge increaseth sorrow.
verses.verse_html: 18For in much wisdom is much grief: and he that increaseth knowledge increaseth sorrow.
